<CENTER><H3>
In the Dark Shadow: Enharmonic Equivalence as Subtext in Two Wolf <I>Lieder</I></H3>
<a href="http://www-student.furman.edu/users/r/rkelley/" target="_top">Robert T. Kelley</a><p>
</CENTER>

<HR>

<P class="firstline">Here you will find the paper I delivered at the 2003 Hugo Wolf Symposium at Florida State University.  In addition to interpretation based on enharmonic progressions, I have also begun looking at directional tonality in Wolf's songs.  Feel free to contact me about my work with enharmonic progressions and directional tonality in this and other repertoires that use chromatic harmony: &lt;<script>

